<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Description ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''BIM Slab''' tool creates a '''Slab''' object, a horizontal structure element, from a planar shape. Slabs are specialized [[Arch_Structure|Arch Structure]] objects with their {{PropertyData|Ifc Type}} preset to "Slab".
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
While it behaves like a standard Arch Structure, the BIM tool specifically initializes the slab with a default height (thickness) of 200 mm and an extrusion direction pointing downwards.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Usage==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Optionally select a planar object.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:BIM_Slab.svg|16px]] [[BIM_Slab|Slab]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|3D/BIM → [[Image:BIM_Slab.svg|16px]] Slab}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|S}} then {{KEY|B}}.
# If you have not yet selected a planar object: select one (as prompted in the [[Report_View|Report View]]).
# A new Slab object is created and the tool is finished.
# Optionally change some properties in the [[Property_View|Property View]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Notes==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Wrapping behavior''': the tool "wraps" the selected object. If you select a sub-element (like a face in the 3D view), the tool identifies the parent object and uses that as the {{PropertyData|Base}}.
* '''Thickness''': to change the thickness of the slab, modify the {{PropertyData|Height}} property.
* '''Orientation''': To make the slab extrude upwards, change the {{PropertyData|Normal}} property to {{Value|(0, 0, 1)}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Properties==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
A Slab object shares the common properties and behaviors of all [[Arch_Structure|Arch Structures]]. Its {{PropertyData|IfcType}} is preset to {{Value|Slab}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Scripting==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The BIM Slab is created using the same Python function as Arch Structures:
</div>

{{Code|code=
import FreeCAD
import Arch
import Draft

# Create a rectangle profile
rect = Draft.make_rectangle(length=2000, width=3000)
FreeCAD.ActiveDocument.recompute()

# Create a structure and define it as a slab
slab = Arch.makeStructure(rect)
slab.IfcType = "Slab"
slab.Height = 150  # mm
slab.Normal = (0, 0, -1)  # Slab is extruded downwards

FreeCAD.ActiveDocument.recompute()
}}


